# PG Access Management Dashboard

A self-service web dashboard to manage PostgreSQL user roles and permissions across multiple GCP-hosted database servers — without writing SQL manually.

---

## What it does

- Register multiple PostgreSQL servers (GCP or any host) from a single dashboard
- Import and browse all existing roles/users from each server
- Grant **SELECT** (read-only) or **SELECT + UPDATE** access to specific databases or tables
- Set **time-bound access** — permissions are automatically revoked when they expire
- Create new PostgreSQL roles with generated or custom passwords
- Manage dashboard users with an allowlist (only approved users can log in)

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React 19, Vite, React Router v6 |
| Backend | Node.js, Express |
| App Database | PostgreSQL |
| Auth | JWT (username + password) |
| Scheduling | node-cron (auto-revocation every 5 min) |
| Deployment | Kubernetes (GCP) |

---

## Features

### Server Management
- Add PostgreSQL servers via direct connection string
- Test connection before saving
- Server credentials encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM)
- Sync and display all existing roles per server

### Permission Grants
- Grant access to **all tables** or **selected tables** in a database
- Optional **UPDATE permission** (always requires an expiry date)
- Time-bound access with automatic revocation via background cron job
- Full grant history with granted-by tracking

### User Management (Admin)
- Create dashboard users with username + password
- Block/unblock users without deleting them
- Admin vs regular user roles

### UI
- Light and dark mode
- Role search with autocomplete across all servers
- Filter grants by server, database, or role/user name
- Password generator (16 chars: a–z, A–Z, 0–9, `!`)

---

## Project Structure

pg-access-management-dashboard/
├── backend/
│   ├── migrations/          # SQL schema files
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── config/          # DB connection, migration runner
│   │   ├── middleware/      # JWT auth
│   │   ├── routes/          # auth, users, servers, grants
│   │   ├── utils/           # AES encryption, role sync
│   │   └── workers/         # Auto-revocation cron job
│   └── .env.example
└── frontend/
└── src/
├── api/             # Axios client
├── components/      # Navbar, Modal, ProtectedRoute
├── context/         # Auth context
├── hooks/           # useTheme
└── pages/           # Login, Servers, DatabaseView, Grants, Users



---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- PostgreSQL (for the app's own data)

### Backend

```bash
cd backend
cp .env.example .env        # fill in your values
npm install
npm run migrate             # creates tables, seeds admin user
npm run dev
Frontend

cd frontend
cp .env.example .env
npm install
npm run dev
Default login
Username	Password
admin	changeme
Change the admin password immediately after first login.

Environment Variables
Backend (.env)
Variable	Description
APP_DB_*	App database connection
JWT_SECRET	Random secret for signing login tokens
ENCRYPTION_KEY	64-char hex key for encrypting stored server passwords
PORT	Backend port (default 3001)
FRONTEND_ORIGIN	CORS allowed origin
Generate secrets:


# JWT_SECRET
openssl rand -base64 48

# ENCRYPTION_KEY
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
⚠️ Never change ENCRYPTION_KEY after going live without migrating existing encrypted data.

Frontend (.env)
Variable	Description
VITE_API_URL	Backend API base URL
Production (Kubernetes)
Store secrets in Kubernetes Secrets or GCP Secret Manager — never in files on the server.


kubectl create secret generic pg-dashboard-secrets \
  --from-literal=JWT_SECRET="..." \
  --from-literal=ENCRYPTION_KEY="..."
Reference in deployment YAML:


env:
  - name: JWT_SECRET
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: pg-dashboard-secrets
        key: JWT_SECRET
  - name: ENCRYPTION_KEY
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: pg-dashboard-secrets
        key: ENCRYPTION_KEY
API Overview
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/api/auth/login	Login
GET	/api/servers	List servers
POST	/api/servers	Register server
POST	/api/servers/test-connection	Test DB connection
POST	/api/servers/:id/sync-roles	Import roles from server
GET	/api/servers/:id/databases	List databases
GET	/api/servers/:id/databases/:db/tables	List tables
GET	/api/grants	List grants (filterable)
POST	/api/grants	Create grant
DELETE	/api/grants/:id	Revoke grant
GET	/api/users	List dashboard users (admin)
POST	/api/users	Create dashboard user (admin)


